      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just \"bots\" though. the things being posted are things only i would know, like specific jokes or ways i phrase things. it's like the \"me\" that everyone knows is just... running on autopilot without me. if someone used a massive dataset of my old posts to train a private model, wouldn't it be basically indistinguishable from me? i feel like i'm being replaced in real time.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
